                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A new attachment object or "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "nil"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " if the object could not be created."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The behavior created by this method acts like a solid rod connecting each item to the specified anchor point. Each item is free to rotate around the anchor point, inscribing a circle whose radius is the defined at creation time by the distance between "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "point"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and the item’s center. When forces act on one or both items, the anchor point and other item also move accordingly. The anchor point of the attachment does not interact with collision boundaries."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiattachmentbehavior/1621307-frictiontorque"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to control the rotational behavior of the items. When the value of that property is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", items rotate freely in response to almost any impulse. Adding torque increases the amount of force that must be applied to an item before it rotates."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiattachmentbehavior/1621294-attachmentrange"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to limit the amount of rotation for each item. This property lets you specify the minimum and maximum amount of rotation of the items from their starting positions. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
